<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4 pt-3 pb-3">Welcome</h1>
    <h2>Base Project Template For ASP.NET Core @Model.DotNetCoreVersion Razor Pages Web Application  </h2>
    <h3>This template has no user Authentication</h3>
    <p>Also It uses the bootstrap 4.5.3 framework as default UI. </p>
    <p>Learn about <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/aspnet/core" rel="noreferrer">building Web apps with ASP.NET Core</a>.</p>


    <p>The template extends the existing Visual Studio  ASP.NET Core Razor pages web template project with most helpful features to build a professional web site.</p>
</div>

<div class="card text-center mt-5">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h1>Additional features included in this template: </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-text">
            This project also demonstrates how to add commonly used custom UI features in the Visual Studio 2019 Community edition.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-footer text-muted">
        <p class="card-text">
            This template does NOT demonstrates how to add custom user data to a generated project in the Visual Studio 2019 Comunity edition. Please check the other template that comes with user authentication enabled. And it will show the practices used to meet some of the GDPR requirements added custom user data, ie user can delete own user data entered any time.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

